  <title>Experiencing Newton's Third Law of Motion</title>
    
  <introduction>
    <p>
      The idea of objects pushing back on us is not necessarily an intuitive one. We are going to do a series of activities to try to develop a deeper sense
      of what it means in practice.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <paragraphs>
    <title>Instructions</title>

    <p>
      Instructions: Sit on a dolly. Throw light things off of it. Then heavier and heavier. 
    </p>

